  "prompt": "How do I check my last 3 charges in Vodafone?",
  "response": "To check your last three charges with Vodafone, you can typically use one of the following methods:\n\n1. **My Vodafone App**: \n   - Open the My Vodafone app on your smartphone.\n   - Log in with your Vodafone account credentials.\n   - Navigate to the billing section, often labeled as \"Bills\" or \"Usage\" where you can view recent charges and possibly download detailed statements.\n\n2. **Vodafone Website**:\n   - Go to the official Vodafone website.\n   - Log in to your account.\n   - Look for a section related to billing or account history to view recent charges and download your bill if needed.\n\n3. **USSD Codes**:\n   - Depending on your country, Vodafone might provide USSD codes to check your recent charges or balance. A common one is `*111#`, but you should verify this with your local Vodafone customer service.\n\n4. **Customer Service**:\n   - Call Vodafone customer service and ask them to provide details regarding your last three charges.\n   - You may be required to verify your identity for security reasons.\n\n5. **Text Message**:\n   - Some regions offer a service where you can send a specific keyword via SMS to a designated number to receive billing information. Check with Vodafone support for details.\n\nMake sure you're aware of any charges that might apply when using these services and that you have access to your account credentials to use online services effectively.",
